main event: A white, metallic-looking object was spotted in the sky over Queens, New York on October 1, 1967.
interesting points: The object made a 360 degree arc and was described as 'pulsating' with a red light.
The object was observed for about 45 minutes, moving at a speed of 30-35 mph.
The object was estimated to be about 2'x5' in size.
Several residents in the Bayside area of Queens witnessed the object.
The object made a humming or buzzing noise and faded away gradually until it could no longer be seen.
sighted object: a white, metallic-looking object with a pulsating red light
witnesses: multiple residents in the Bayside area
photographs: no photographs present in the report
